The greenhouse gas emissions for subpart W (oil and natural gas systems) facilities are calculated by identifying all fluorinated GHGs with emissions of 1,000 metric tons CO2e or more from production and transformation processes, summed across the facility as a whole. Additionally, the calculated annual CO2, CH4, and N2O emissions for each unit must be reported, along with the applicable equation input parameters specified in paragraphs (f)(7) through (f)(13) of the section. The total annual emissions across fluorinated GHGs for the entire facility, in metric tons of CO2e, are calculated using the default GWP of 10,000. Furthermore, the emissions from production and transformation processes of fluorinated GHGs by fluorinated GHG group for the facility as a whole must be reported, with the exception of a major fluorinated GHG constituent of a fluorinated gas product, if applicable. The total GWP-weighted mass of all fluorinated GHGs in each group emitted from equipment leaks must also be reported in metric tons of CO2e.{
