If you do not have a continuous gas composition analyzer for feed natural gas, then you must take annual samples according to methods set forth in § 98.234(b) to determine the GHG mole fraction. Additionally, for local distribution pipeline natural gas and natural gas stored in the LNG import and export industry segment, you may use either a default 95 percent methane and 1 percent carbon dioxide fraction for GHG mole fraction in natural gas or site-specific engineering estimates based on best available data. For onshore natural gas production and onshore petroleum and natural gas gathering and boosting, if you have a continuous gas composition analyzer for produced natural gas, you must use an annual average of these values for determining the mole fraction. If you do not have a continuous gas composition analyzer, then you must use an annual average gas composition based on your most recent available analysis of the sub-basin category or facility, as applicable to the emission source.{
